stimulus:
In this experiment, you will be shown 30 images of 5 wild bee species and be asked to solve three tasks.

Task 1 (10 images): Assign a species to the test image based on the prototypes shown on the right half of the page.

Task 2 (10 images): Assign a species while also knowing our model's prediction (marked red in title).

Task 3 (10 images): Assign again a species only with the help of the prototypes (no model prediction revealed).

Note: From this moment on, please avoid resizing your browser window, as this may cause the zooming tool to malfunction.

stimulus:
In this experiment, you will be shown 30 images of 5 wild bee species and be asked to solve three tasks.

Task 1 (10 images): Assign a species to the test image based on the prototypes shown on the right half of the page.

Task 2 (10 images): Assign a species while also knowing our model's prediction and seeing an explanation for it (marked red in title).

Task 3 (10 images): Assign again a species only with the help of the prototypes (no model prediction revealed).

After these tasks, you will be asked to rate 4 statements regarding your experience throughout the experiment.

Note: From this moment on, please avoid resizing your browser window, as this may cause the zooming tool to malfunction.

Andrena flavipes

Bombus lucorum

Task 1 (10 images): Assign a species to the test image based on the prototypes.

stimulus:
In this experiment, you will be shown 30 images of 5 wild bee species and be asked to solve three tasks.

Task 1 (10 images): Assign a species to the test image based on the prototypes shown on the right half of the page.

Task 2 (10 images): Assign a species while also knowing our model's prediction and seeing an explanation for it (marked red in title).

Task 3 (10 images): Assign again a species only with the help of the prototypes (no model prediction revealed).

After these tasks, you will be asked to rate 4 statements regarding your experience throughout the experiment.

Note: From this moment on, please avoid resizing your browser window, as this may cause the zooming tool to malfunction.

stimulus:
In this experiment, you will be shown 30 images of 5 wild bee species and be asked to solve three tasks.

Task 1 (10 images): Assign a species to the test image based on the prototypes shown on the right half of the page.

Task 2 (10 images): Assign a species while also knowing our model's prediction (marked red in title).

Task 3 (10 images): Assign again a species only with the help of the prototypes (no model prediction revealed).

Note: From this moment on, please avoid resizing your browser window, as this may cause the zooming tool to malfunction.

Task 1 (10 images): Assign a species to the test image based on the prototypes.

stimulus:
In this experiment, you will be shown 30 images of 5 wild bee species and be asked to solve three tasks.

Task 1 (10 images): Assign a species to the test image based on the prototypes shown on the right half of the page.

Task 2 (10 images): Assign a species while also knowing our model's prediction and seeing an explanation for it (marked red in title).

Task 3 (10 images): Assign again a species only with the help of the prototypes (no model prediction revealed).

After these tasks, you will be asked to rate 4 statements regarding your experience throughout the experiment.

Note: From this moment on, please avoid resizing your browser window, as this may cause the zooming tool to malfunction.

Whenever you are ready, click Continue to start the first task:

Task 1 (10 images): Assign a species to the test image based on the prototypes.

stimulus:
In this experiment, you will be shown 30 images of 5 wild bee species and be asked to solve three tasks.

Task 1 (10 images): Assign a species to the test image based on the prototypes shown on the right half of the page.

Task 2 (10 images): Assign a species while also knowing our model's prediction and seeing an explanation for it (marked red in title).

Task 3 (10 images): Assign again a species only with the help of the prototypes (no model prediction revealed).

After these tasks, you will be asked to rate 4 statements regarding your experience throughout the experiment.

Note: From this moment on, please avoid resizing your browser window, as this may cause the zooming tool to malfunction.

stimulus:
In this experiment, you will be shown 30 images of 5 wild bee species and be asked to solve three tasks.

Note: From this moment on, please avoid resizing your browser window, as this may cause the zooming tool to malfunction.

stimulus:
In this experiment, you will be shown 30 images of 5 wild bee species and be asked to solve three tasks.

Task 1 (10 images): Assign a species to the test image based on the prototypes shown on the right half of the page.

Task 2 (10 images): Assign a species while also knowing our model's prediction and seeing an explanation for it (marked red in title).

Task 3 (10 images): Assign again a species only with the help of the prototypes (no model prediction revealed).

After these tasks, you will be asked to rate 4 statements regarding your experience throughout the experiment.

Note: From this moment on, please avoid resizing your browser window, as this may cause the zooming tool to malfunction.

Task 1 (10 images): Assign a species to the test image based on the prototypes.
